## Core Principles (THE RULES)

### 1. DATA QUALITY > SPEED
```
- No mock data EVER in production
- Log every missing/failed data fetch
- Gracefully degrade (skip signal) if data incomplete
- Historical validation required for all new data sources
```

### 2. CONFIRMATION > CONVICTION
```
- Never act on single factor
- Require 3+ confirmations for any signal
- Higher confidence = larger position size (within 2% limit)
- When in doubt, sit out
```

### 3. RISK MANAGEMENT > PROFIT CHASING
```
- Stop loss ALWAYS set before entry
- Never move stop further from entry
- Exit immediately if thesis invalidated
- 5% daily drawdown = STOP TRADING for the day
```

### 4. BACKTESTING > INTUITION
```
- Every new strategy MUST backtest on historical data
- Paper trade BEFORE live capital
- Track ALL metrics: win rate, R/R, max DD, Sharpe ratio
- Kill strategies that don't show edge after 30 trades
```

### 5. SIMPLICITY > COMPLEXITY
```
- Focus on SPY/QQQ only (master these first)
- 3-4 signal types max
- Clear entry/exit criteria
- If you can't explain it in 30 seconds, it's too complex
```

### 6. CONTINUOUS LEARNING
```
- Review EVERY trade (win or loss)
- Journal: What worked? What didn't? Why?
- Update thresholds based on data
- Archive all signals for future ML training
```

